10/11/2006
MOSCOW, Russia -- Bulgarian Interior Minister Rumen Petkov and his Russian counterpart, Rashid Nurgaliev, signed an agreement Friday (November 10th) on co-operation in the fight against organised crime. 
The accord stipulates 15 areas of collaboration, including terrorism, drug, human and weapons trafficking, money laundering and car thefts. 
The document also envisions regular exchange of information and the formation of common anti-crime teams and joint training programmes within the Russia's training centres for fight against terrorism. 
(News.bg, Focus - 10/11/06)
